        <li class="project" id="AzureCookbook">
            <div>
                <a href="https://github.com/MWight20/Azure_Cookbook" id="projectTitleLink"><h2><strong>Azure Cookbook</strong></h2></a>
                <a href="~/Content/Images/azurecookbookscreenshot.png"><img src="~/Content/Images/azurecookbookscreenshot.png" id="sampleProjectImg" /></a>
                <a href="~/Content/Images/AzureCookBookNewRecipe.png"><img src="~/Content/Images/AzureCookBookNewRecipe.png" id="sampleProjectImg" /></a>

                <p id="imageEnlarge"><small>Click on image to enlarge</small></p>

                <div class="projectContentDescription">
                    <p><strong>Azure Cookbook</strong></p>
                    <p>
                        This cookbook app serves as a means to organize and collect different cooking recipes into one place and manage them into a viewable, navigatable user interface.
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        Anybody can view individual recipes via a main community page hub. You can add a new recipe to the community page either as a guest or as a registered user. Guests will not be able
                        to return and edit their recipes.
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        <strong>Technologies used:</strong>
                        <br />
                        C#.NET, MVC, Entity Framework, JavaScript, MySQL, Visual Studio 2017, Bootstrap.
                    </p>

                </div>

                <div class="buttonDiv">
                    <a class="button gitLink" href="https://github.com/MWight20/Azure_Cookbook">
                        Click here to visit on GitHub
                    </a>

                </div>
            </div>
        </li>


